nces in the operations or logistics of Alpha and Omega Leo Clubs.\r\nIn addition to the Alpha and Omega tracks, Leo clubs should also designate whether they are school based or community based.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1094\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/leoLogos.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"160\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Youth interested in joining a Leo club can use the </strong><a href=\"https://directory.lionsclubs.org/?language=EN\"><strong>Club Locator</strong></a><strong> tool to find a Leo club in their community.</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>More Details Links : </strong></span>\r\n\r\nLeo Clubs\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leo_clubs\">Leo Clubs wiki Article</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://members.lionsclubs.org/EN/leos/leadership-opportunities/club-leadership/index.php\">Learn more about Leo Club Leadership.</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://members.lionsclubs.org/EN/leos/leadership-opportunities/leo-districts-multiple-districts.php\">Learn more about Leo Districts and Multiple Districts.</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://members.lionsclubs.org/EN/leos/leadership-opportunities/leo-leadership-grant.php\">Learn more about Leo Leadership Grants.</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://members.lionsclubs.org/EN/leos/leadership-opportunities/advisory-panel.php\">Learn more about the Leo Advisory Panel.</a>', 'LEOISM', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1087-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-12-22 20:52:21', '2017-12-22 15:22:21', '', 1087, 'http://www.uomleos.org/2017/12/22/1087-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1103, 2, '2017-12-22 20:55:54', '2017-12-22 15:25:54', '<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><em>WHAT IS LEOISM ?</em></strong></span></h2>\r\nLeo Club is a youth organisation of <a href=\"http://www.lionsclubs.org/\">Lions Club International.</a> The acronym L.E.O stands for Leadership, Experience, Opportunity.\r\nThe Leo Club objective is, to provide the youth of the world with an opportunity for development and contribution, individually and collectively, as responsible members of the local, national and international community.\r\nLeo Club encourages the youth to develop leadership qualities by participating in social service activities. They are dependent on a Lions club to sponsor and initiate a Leo club. Leo Club members are addressed as \"Leos.\" They conduct various projects in the fields of health care, elders, children, differently abled, literacy and education, and self-development.\r\n​LEO Club is the largest youth club of voluntary character in the world , present in 140 countries with over 160,000 members.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1088\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"200\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1088\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/lionlogo_2c-300x284.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"189\" /> Lions International[/caption]\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><em>WHAT IS THE MOTTO OF LEOISM ?</em></strong></span></h3>\r\n\"To promote service activities among the youth of the community which will develop the individual qualities of Leadership, Experience and Opportunity. To unite its members in friendship, fellowship and mutual understanding.\"\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><em>HOW DID IT ALL START?</em></strong></span></h3>\r\nThe first Leo Club was founded in 1957 by Jim Graver, the coach of the Abington<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abington_Senior_High_School\"> </a>High School, Pennsylvania baseball team. He was an active member of the Glenside Lions Club. The club was founded with the help of William Ernst, another local Lion. It adopted the high school\'s colours of maroon and gold. The club also created the acronym Leadership, Equality, Opportunity for the word Leo. The word equality was later changed to Experience.\r\nIn 1964 the Leo Club Program became a sponsored program of the Lions District. It grew beyond Pennsylvania and the United States of America. By 1967 the program had grown to over 200 clubs in 18 countries and had become an official youth program of Lions Clubs International. In the following year, the Leo Club Program spread rapidly, more than quadrupling in size, to 918 clubs in 48 countries by the end of 1968.\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><em>HOW DOES IT FUNCTION ?</em></strong></span></h3>\r\nLeo clubs make local communities better places to live through a diverse array of community service projects and fellowship events which are conducted on a regular basis. It believes in getting people under one banner to help the society as a whole.\r\n​The basic structure of a Leo Club is as follows:\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The Multiple District</strong>\r\nSeveral Districts comprising of their own Leo Clubs form a Multiple District. The highest post that can be concurred by a Leo is the chair of the Multiple District President.\r\n​e.g. Leo Club of Juhu is a part of Multiple District 3231</h4>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1089\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"200\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1089\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/xaYGTVYd_400x400-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /> Multiple District 3231[/caption]\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The District</strong>\r\nSeveral Leo Clubs in an area make up a District, headed by the District President.\r\ne.g. Leo Club of Juhu is part of District A3 within Multiple District 3231. Cumulatively we refer to the club being a part of District 3231-A3.</h4>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1090\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"164\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1090 size-full\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/district-logo.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"164\" height=\"186\" /> District 323 A3[/caption]\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The Club</strong>\r\nThis is the fundamental level of Leoism. A club, headed by its own President reports to the District which further reports to the Multiple District.</h4>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1091\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"200\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1091\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/ltlltl-logo_1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /> Leo Club of Juhu[/caption]\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><em>LIONS SERVE. WHAT DO LEOS DO ?</em></strong></span></h3>\r\nLeos essentially is a service project of the Lions to build responsible future leaders, but that in no way means that we don\'t serve rather Leo club of Juhu is known for its service legacy.\r\nLeoism is focussed on fellowship. Fellowship refers to socialisation or precisely secondary socialisation. We believe that the process of learning what is the appropriate behaviour as a member of a smaller group within the larger society is an essential part of shaping one\'s personality.\r\n​\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><em>WHAT AGE GROUP CAN JOIN A LEO CLUB ?</em></strong></span></h3>\r\nThere are two tracks of the Leo Club Program. Alpha Leo clubs are those that consist of members between 12 and 18 years of age. Omega Leo clubs are those that consist of members between 18 and 30 years of age.\r\n​The Leo Club Program\'s maximum age of membership is 30 years of age, though it is at the discretion of the Lion\'s district to enforce younger upper-age limits for Omega clubs. There are no major differences in the operations or logistics of Alpha and Omega Leo Clubs.\r\nIn addition to the Alpha and Omega tracks, Leo clubs should also designate whether they are school based or community based.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1094\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/leoLogos.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"160\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Youth interested in joining a Leo club can use the </strong><a href=\"https://directory.lionsclubs.org/?language=EN\"><strong>Club Locator</strong></a><strong> tool to find a Leo club in their community.</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>More Details Links : </strong></span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://members.lionsclubs.org/EN/leos/index.php\">Leo Clubs</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leo_clubs\">Leo Clubs wiki Article</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://members.lionsclubs.org/EN/leos/leadership-opportunities/club-leadership/index.php\">Learn more about Leo Club Leadership.</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://members.lionsclubs.org/EN/leos/leadership-opportunities/leo-districts-multiple-districts.php\">Learn more about Leo Districts and Multiple Districts.</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://members.lionsclubs.org/EN/leos/leadership-opportunities/leo-leadership-grant.php\">Learn more about Leo Leadership Grants.</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://members.lionsclubs.org/EN/leos/leadership-opportunities/advisory-panel.php\">Learn more about the Leo Advisory Panel.</a>', 'LEOISM', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1087-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-12-22 20:55:54', '2017-12-22 15:25:54', '', 1087, 'http://www.uomleos.org/2017/12/22/1087-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1104, 2, '2017-12-22 21:42:59', '2017-12-22 16:12:59', '<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1120 size-full\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/banner.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1366\" height=\"200\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">University of Moratuwa is the most sought after technological university in Sri Lanka and is frequently ranked among the top 10 Universities in the South Asian subcontinents. It oﬀers degree programs to over 8000 undergraduates annually in the faculties of Engineering, Architecture, Information Technology and Business in 18 disciplines</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1105\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"600\"]<img class=\"uomimage wp-image-1105\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/uom1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"415\" /> University of Moratuwa[/caption]\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Fifteen years back a group of undergraduates from University of Moratuwa joined their hands to lay the foundation for the Leo Club of University of Moratuwa. In 2003 with the help of Lion Lester Aponso, District Chairman for Leo\'s of Leo District 306A (2002/2003) and Leo Shyana Wijayaratne, District President of Leo District 306A (2002/2003) and also with the permission of university authority, Leo Club of University of Moratuwa was established in 27th June 2003, as the SECOND university based Leo Club in Sri Lanka and as the FIRST Leo club in Leo District 306A. Lions Club of Dehiwala North, a leading Lions Club in District 306A, provided the sponsorship for the club. On behalf of the university authority, Dr. Saman Thilakasiri took the challenge of the Patron and Mr. Kithsiri Samarasinghe took the responsibility of Senior Treasurer.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_747\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"uomimage wp-image-747 size-medium\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/12938233_574293186078321_4710027151299796369_n-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /> Senior Treasurer : Mr. Kithsiri Samarasinghe[/caption]\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The installation ceremony organized by the parents Lions Club took place on the 27th of July 2003 at Lions Activity Center, Moratuwa. 38 Engineering undergraduates were installed as Charter Members of Leo Club of University of Moratuwa on that day. Under the presidency of Leo Nadun Gunawadena and the guidance of uncle Ravi (Lion Ravi Rajapathirana - Leo Advisor) and the help of DP Leo Shehan the club completed its first Leostic year, being the runner-up for the Most outstanding new club of the district in 25th Annual Leo Conference. Also, the project \"Api Akurata Meli Nowemu\" and \"Leo Paduru Sajjaya\" took the attention of whole Leo District.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The club has never looked back since that day and has continued its expansion and kept multiplying the services to the University and to the community. In Leostic year 2004/2005 the club was led by Leo Mahesh Prasanna Abeywickrama. Unfortunately, he left us at an unexpected moment. Upon his decease Leo Chatura Gunawardane took the lead of the club and he was able to bring it to a greater height. By this time the district was divided in to 2 as A1&amp;A2. With that the club was shifted to district 306A2. The club was re-born with the great leadership of Leo Tharanga Gunasekara (2005/2006). In the inaugural District Conference of district 306A2 we were awarded with 13 project awards, 6 individual awards and five district and club awards. Further, we were crowned as the Most Outstanding Club in the Leo district 306A2.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1109\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"250\"]<img class=\"uomimagepng wp-image-1109 size-full\" style=\"color: #555555; font-size: 17px;\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/md.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" /> Leo District 306[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1108\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"250\"]<img class=\"uomimagepng wp-image-1108 size-full\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/dp.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" /> Leo District 306 A2[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Since then, the Leo club of UoM retained possession of the Most Outstanding Club in the district, and it was proved with the 18 awards achieved at the 2<sup>nd</sup> District Conference under the leadership of Leo Buddhi Hettiarachchi in Leostic year 2006/2007. In Leoistic year 2007/2008 under the presidency of Leo Namal Karunarathne the club was again awarded as the Most outstanding Leo club in the Leo district 306A2 at the 3<sup>rd</sup> Annual District Conference. We achieved 12 project awards, 7 individual awards and 2 district and club awards.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Leo Buddhi Isurujith is the president of the Leo Club of University of Moratuwa for the Leoistic year 2017/18. The current membership of the club is about 89 members.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_62\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"uomimage wp-image-62 size-medium\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/07-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /> Current President : Leo Budhdhi Isurujith[/caption]\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">From the beginning, Leo Club of University of Moratuwa has been actively involving in community service projects while enhancing leadership skills of University students. In the District Conference of 306A2, Leo Club of University of Moratuwa was the first runner up for the Most Outstanding Leo club of the District for the year 2016/2017. Leo Club of University of Moratuwa also won the Most Outstanding University Leo Club in Sri Lanka in the Leo Multiple District Conference and rewarded as the winners in Youth Leadership and Empowerment project, project on spotlight on Children, Multi Service project and project on Public Relationship, Communication and Marketing. Most importantly Leo Club of University of Moratuwa remains as one of the best and active student societies within the University where, a fortress made of dynamic youngsters are congregated to serve the community.</p>', 'UoM Leos', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'uom-leos', '', '', '2018-01-02 16:42:37', '2018-01-02 11:12:37', '', 0, 'http://www.uomleos.org/?page_id=1104', 0, 'page', '', 0),
