tion id=\"attachment_1404\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1404 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/10-any-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> 10th Anniversary Celebration of UoM Leos - 2013[/caption]\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2014</strong></h3>\r\nUnder the Leadership of Leo Ajith Ranaweera, UoM Leos were successfully granted with the award of most outstanding Leo club, as many of former years, from PDP Leo Buddika Lakmal Gunasekara in the multiple conference held at defense school auditorium on July 2014.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1405\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1405 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/multiple-conf-2014-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> Awarded UoM Leos by Leo Multiple District - 2014[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1406\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1406 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/multiple-conf-2014_2-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> UoM Leos representing the Leo Multiple District Conference - 2014[/caption]\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2015</strong></h3>\r\nAwarded as the Winner of the Leo district contest, for the excellence service provided towards the society and for the excessive support given to the Leo district 306, throughout the Leostic year 2014/2015, with the leadership of Leo Shehan Madushanka.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1408\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1408 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/12th-Installation_2-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> 12th Installation Ceremony - 2015[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1409\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1409 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/district-Conf_2015-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> Leo District 306 A2 Conference - 2015[/caption]\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2016</strong></h3>\r\nLeo Club of University of Moratuwa awarded as the most outstanding Leo club of the Leo Multiple district 306 – Sri Lanka, Under the Leadership of Leo Ivan Udakara from PMDP Leo Dumidu Jayakody.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1410\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1410 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/13-installation-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> 13th Installation Ceremony - 2016[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1413\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1413 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/13612356_10153973841263369_1070856138815435737_n-300x122.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"163\" /> Leo District 306 A2 Conference - 2016[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1414\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1414 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2016_multiple_conf-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> Most Outstanding University Leo Club Winning Stage (Leo Multiple District 306 Conference) - 2016[/caption]\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2017</strong></h3>\r\nUoM Leos were awarded for being the most outstanding University Leo club of the Leo Multiple district 306 – Sri Lanka, Under the Leadership of Leo Shehan Akmeemana, from PMDP Leo Rajitha Abeygunasekara.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1455\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1455 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/14th-Ins-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> 14th Installation Ceremony - 2017[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1457\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"uomimage wp-image-1457\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/bestleoclub_winning-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> Best University Leo Club Winning Stage - 2017[/caption]', 'Journey Towards Excellence', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1368-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-01-02 17:52:10', '2018-01-02 12:22:10', '', 1368, 'http://www.uomleos.org/2018/01/02/1368-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1542, 2, '2018-01-02 17:53:31', '2018-01-02 12:23:31', '<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>WHAT IS LEOISM ?</strong></span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Leo Club is a youth organisation of <a href=\"http://www.lionsclubs.org/\">Lions Club International.</a> The acronym L.E.O stands for Leadership, Experience, Opportunity.\r\nThe Leo Club objective is, to provide the youth of the world with an opportunity for development and contribution, individually and collectively, as responsible members of the local, national and international community.\r\nLeo Club encourages the youth to develop leadership qualities by participating in social service activities. They are dependent on a Lions club to sponsor and initiate a Leo club. Leo Club members are addressed as \"Leos.\" They conduct various projects in the fields of health care, elders, children, differently abled, literacy and education, and self-development.\r\n​LEO Club is the largest youth club of voluntary character in the world , present in 140 countries with over 160,000 members.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1088\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"200\"]<img class=\"uomimagepng wp-image-1088\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/lionlogo_2c-300x284.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"189\" /> Lions International[/caption]\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>WHAT IS THE MOTTO OF LEOISM ?</strong></span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\"To promote service activities among the youth of the community which will develop the individual qualities of Leadership, Experience and Opportunity. To unite its members in friendship, fellowship and mutual understanding.\"</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>HOW DID IT ALL START?</strong></span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The first Leo Club was founded in 1957 by Jim Graver, the coach of the Abington<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abington_Senior_High_School\"> </a>High School, Pennsylvania baseball team. He was an active member of the Glenside Lions Club. The club was founded with the help of William Ernst, another local Lion. It adopted the high school\'s colours of maroon and gold. The club also created the acronym Leadership, Equality, Opportunity for the word Leo. The word equality was later changed to Experience.\r\nIn 1964 the Leo Club Program became a sponsored program of the Lions District. It grew beyond Pennsylvania and the United States of America. By 1967 the program had grown to over 200 clubs in 18 countries and had become an official youth program of Lions Clubs International. In the following year, the Leo Club Program spread rapidly, more than quadrupling in size, to 918 clubs in 48 countries by the end of 1968.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>HOW DOES IT FUNCTION ?</strong></span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Leo clubs make local communities better places to live through a diverse array of community service projects and fellowship events which are conducted on a regular basis. It believes in getting people under one banner to help the society as a whole.\r\n​The basic structure of a Leo Club is as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The Multiple District</strong>\r\nSeveral Districts comprising of their own Leo Clubs form a Multiple District.The highest position a Leo can get is the position of International Panelist and that is higher than Multiple District presidency.\r\n​e.g. Leo Multiple District 306 Sri Lanka</h4>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1109\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"250\"]<img class=\"uomimagepng wp-image-1109 size-full\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/md.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" /> Leo Multiple District 306 Sri Lanka[/caption]\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The District</strong>\r\nSeveral Leo Clubs in an area make up a District, headed by the District President.\r\ne.g. Leo Club of University of Moratuwa is part of District A2 within Multiple District 306. Cumulatively we refer to the club being a part of District 306-A2.</h4>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1108\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"250\"]<img class=\"uomimagepng wp-image-1108 size-full\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/dp.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" /> Leo District 306 A2[/caption]\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The Club</strong>\r\nThis is the fundamental level of Leoism. A club, headed by its own President reports to the District which further reports to the Multiple District. e.g. : Leo Club of University of Moratuwa</h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>LIONS SERVE. WHAT DO LEOS DO ?</strong></span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Leos essentially is a service project of the Lions to build responsible future leaders, but that in no way means that we don\'t serve rather Leo club of Juhu is known for its service legacy.\r\nLeoism is focussed on fellowship. Fellowship refers to socialisation or precisely secondary socialisation. We believe that the process of learning what is the appropriate behaviour as a member of a smaller group within the larger society is an essential part of shaping one\'s personality.\r\n​</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>WHAT AGE GROUP CAN JOIN A LEO CLUB ?</strong></span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">There are two tracks of the Leo Club Program. Alpha Leo clubs are those that consist of members between 12 and 18 years of age. Omega Leo clubs are those that consist of members between 18 and 30 years of age.\r\n​The Leo Club Program\'s maximum age of membership is 30 years of age, though it is at the discretion of the Lion\'s district to enforce younger upper-age limits for Omega clubs. There are no major differences in the operations or logistics of Alpha and Omega Leo Clubs.\r\nIn addition to the Alpha and Omega tracks, Leo clubs should also designate whether they are school based or community based.</p>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1094\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/leoLogos.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"160\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Youth interested in joining a Leo club can use the </strong><a href=\"https://directory.lionsclubs.org/?language=EN\"><strong>Club Locator</strong></a><strong> tool to find a Leo club in their community.</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>More Details Links : </strong></span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://members.lionsclubs.org/EN/leos/index.php\">Leo Clubs</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leo_clubs\">Leo Clubs wiki Article</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://members.lionsclubs.org/EN/leos/leadership-opportunities/club-leadership/index.php\">Learn more about Leo Club Leadership.</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://members.lionsclubs.org/EN/leos/leadership-opportunities/leo-districts-multiple-districts.php\">Learn more about Leo Districts and Multiple Districts.</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://members.lionsclubs.org/EN/leos/leadership-opportunities/leo-leadership-grant.php\">Learn more about Leo Leadership Grants.</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://members.lionsclubs.org/EN/leos/leadership-opportunities/advisory-panel.php\">Learn more about the Leo Advisory Panel.</a>', 'LEOISM', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1087-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-01-02 17:53:31', '2018-01-02 12:23:31', '', 1087, 'http://www.uomleos.org/2018/01/02/1087-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1543, 2, '2018-01-02 18:04:08', '2018-01-02 12:34:08', '<h2 align=\"center\"><strong>~The Path We Came~</strong></h2>\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2003</strong></h3>\r\nLeo club of University of Moratuwa was started on 27th of July 2003 at Lions Activity Center, Moratuwa and 38 Engineering undergraduates were installed as Charter Members on that day, under the presidency of Leo Nadun Gunawadena.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1386\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1386 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/1st-installation-300x204.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"272\" /> 1st installation Ceremony - 2003[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1384\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1384 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/1st-director-bord-2003-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> 1st Director board 2003[/caption]\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2004</strong></h3>\r\nLeo club of University of Moratuwa completed its first Leostic year, being the runner-up for the most outstanding new club of the district, 306A, in 25th Annual Leo Conference held on July 2004.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1399\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1399 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2nd-instadire-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> 2nd Installation / 2nd Director Board[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1400\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"uomimage wp-image-1400\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/best-new-club-pre-2004-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> Receiving best new club 1st Runner up award - 2004[/caption]\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2005</strong></h3>\r\nLeo District 306A was Divided in to District as A1 and A2. With that Leo Club of University of Moratuwa was shifted to district 306A2.\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2006</strong></h3>\r\nYear 2006 was a remarkable milestone in the history of UoM Leos, as the club got the opportunity to win the award “The most outstanding club of Leo district 306A2” for the first time in the inaugural District Conference of Leo district 306A2 held on July 2005 with 13 project awards, 6 individual awards and 5 district and club awards.\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2007</strong></h3>\r\nLeo club of University of Moratuwa again awarded as the Most Outstanding Leo Club of the district and the victory was confirmed with the 18 awards achieved at the 2<sup>nd</sup>District Conference, under the leadership of Leo Buddhi Hettiarachchi. At the same time Leo Tharanga Gunasekar was awarded as the Leo of the Year for year 2006/2007.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1402\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1402 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/camp-2007-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> Leo Camp - 2007[/caption]\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2008</strong></h3>\r\nIn the year 2008, under the presidency of Leo Namal Karunarathne the Leo club of University of Moratuwa was awarded as the Most outstanding Leo club in the Leo district 306A2 for the consecutive 3<sup>rd</sup> time at the 3<sup>rd</sup> Annual District Conference. UoM Leos achieved 12 project awards, 7 individual awards and 2 district and club awards.\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2009</strong></h3>\r\nContinuing the Excellency, for the consecutive 4<sup>th</sup> time Most Outstanding Leo club of the Leo District 306 A2 was won by UoM Leos, at the yearend conference. Further, Leo Isuru Senadeera, an excellent leader produced by the club, was awarded as the Leo of the year for the Leostic year 2008/2009.\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2011</strong></h3>\r\nFor the year 2011 Leo club of University of Moratuwa was awarded as the 2<sup>nd</sup> Runner up of the Leo District contest at the Leo District conference held at Hotel Galadari, under the leadership of Leo Damith Amarakon from PDP Leo Thilini Manamperi.\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2012</strong></h3>\r\nUoM Leos were Lucky to produce first ever Leo District president to the Leo District 306 A2, from their own club in this year. And also they were blessed with the award of most outstanding Leo club of Leo Multiple district 306 – Sri Lanka, under the Leadership of Leo Naveen Thameera, from PMDP Leo Thiruparan Siwapathasudaram.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1403\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"uomimage wp-image-1403\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/1st-ever-DP-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> First ever district president produced by UoM Leos to Leo District 306 A2 - 2012[/caption]\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2013</strong></h3>\r\nLeo Club of University of Moratuwa Celebrated their 10<sup>th</sup> year anniversary, recalling their journey of pride and remarkable. In this year too, the award of Most Outstanding Leo Club, of the Leo district 306 A2, was won by Leo club of university of moratuwa ander the Leadership of Leo Chathuranga Gunasekara\r\n