(1544, 2, '2018-01-02 18:09:39', '2018-01-02 12:39:39', '<h2 align=\"center\"><strong>~The Path We Came~</strong></h2>\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2003</strong></h3>\r\nLeo club of University of Moratuwa was started on 27th of July 2003 at Lions Activity Center, Moratuwa and 38 Engineering undergraduates were installed as Charter Members on that day, under the presidency of Leo Nadun Gunawadena.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1386\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1386 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/1st-installation-300x204.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"272\" /> 1st installation Ceremony - 2003[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1384\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1384 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/1st-director-bord-2003-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> 1st Director board 2003[/caption]\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2004</strong></h3>\r\nLeo club of University of Moratuwa completed its first Leostic year, being the runner-up for the most outstanding new club of the district, 306A, in 25th Annual Leo Conference held on July 2004.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1399\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1399 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2nd-instadire-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> 2nd Installation / 2nd Director Board[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1400\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"uomimage wp-image-1400\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/best-new-club-pre-2004-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> Receiving best new club 1st Runner up award - 2004[/caption]\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2005</strong></h3>\r\nLeo District 306A was Divided in to District as A1 and A2. With that Leo Club of University of Moratuwa was shifted to district 306A2.\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2006</strong></h3>\r\nYear 2006 was a remarkable milestone in the history of UoM Leos, as the club got the opportunity to win the award “The most outstanding club of Leo district 306A2” for the first time in the inaugural District Conference of Leo district 306A2 held on July 2005 with 13 project awards, 6 individual awards and 5 district and club awards.\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2007</strong></h3>\r\nLeo club of University of Moratuwa again awarded as the Most Outstanding Leo Club of the district and the victory was confirmed with the 18 awards achieved at the 2<sup>nd</sup>District Conference, under the leadership of Leo Buddhi Hettiarachchi. At the same time Leo Tharanga Gunasekar was awarded as the Leo of the Year for year 2006/2007.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1402\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1402 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/camp-2007-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> Leo Camp - 2007[/caption]\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2008</strong></h3>\r\nIn the year 2008, under the presidency of Leo Namal Karunarathne the Leo club of University of Moratuwa was awarded as the Most outstanding Leo club in the Leo district 306A2 for the consecutive 3<sup>rd</sup> time at the 3<sup>rd</sup> Annual District Conference. UoM Leos achieved 12 project awards, 7 individual awards and 2 district and club awards.\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2009</strong></h3>\r\nContinuing the Excellency, for the consecutive 4<sup>th</sup> time Most Outstanding Leo club of the Leo District 306 A2 was won by UoM Leos, at the yearend conference. Further, Leo Isuru Senadeera, an excellent leader produced by the club, was awarded as the Leo of the year for the Leostic year 2008/2009.\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2011</strong></h3>\r\nFor the year 2011 Leo club of University of Moratuwa was awarded as the 2<sup>nd</sup> Runner up of the Leo District contest at the Leo District conference held at Hotel Galadari, under the leadership of Leo Damith Amarakon from PDP Leo Thilini Manamperi.\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2012</strong></h3>\r\nUoM Leos were Lucky to produce first ever Leo District president to the Leo District 306 A2, from their own club in this year. And also they were blessed with the award of most outstanding Leo club of Leo Multiple district 306 – Sri Lanka, under the Leadership of Leo Naveen Thameera, from PMDP Leo Thiruparan Siwapathasudaram.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1403\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"uomimage wp-image-1403\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/1st-ever-DP-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> First ever district president produced by UoM Leos to Leo District 306 A2 - 2012[/caption]\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2013</strong></h3>\r\nLeo Club of University of Moratuwa Celebrated their 10<sup>th</sup> year anniversary, recalling their journey of pride and remarkable. In this year too, the award of Most Outstanding Leo Club, of the Leo district 306 A2, was won by Leo club of university of moratuwa ander the Leadership of Leo Chathuranga Gunasekara\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1404\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1404 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/10-any-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> 10th Anniversary Celebration of UoM Leos - 2013[/caption]\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2014</strong></h3>\r\nUnder the Leadership of Leo Ajith Ranaweera, UoM Leos were successfully granted with the award of most outstanding Leo club, as many of former years, from PDP Leo Buddika Lakmal Gunasekara in the multiple conference held at defense school auditorium on July 2014.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1405\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1405 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/multiple-conf-2014-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> Awarded UoM Leos by Leo Multiple District - 2014[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1406\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1406 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/multiple-conf-2014_2-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> UoM Leos representing the Leo Multiple District Conference - 2014[/caption]\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2015</strong></h3>\r\nAwarded as the Winner of the Leo district contest, for the excellence service provided towards the society and for the excessive support given to the Leo district 306, throughout the Leostic year 2014/2015, with the leadership of Leo Shehan Madushanka.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1408\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1408 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/12th-Installation_2-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> 12th Installation Ceremony - 2015[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1409\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1409 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/district-Conf_2015-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> Conference - Leo District 306 A2  - 2015[/caption]\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2016</strong></h3>\r\nLeo Club of University of Moratuwa awarded as the most outstanding Leo club of the Leo Multiple district 306 – Sri Lanka, Under the Leadership of Leo Ivan Udakara from PMDP Leo Dumidu Jayakody.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1410\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1410 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/13-installation-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> 13th Installation Ceremony - 2016[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1413\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1413 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/13612356_10153973841263369_1070856138815435737_n-300x122.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"163\" /> Leo District 306 A2 Conference - 2016[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1414\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"uomimage wp-image-1414\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/2016_multiple_conf-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> Most outstanding Leo Club winners on the stage - 2016[/caption]\r\n<h3><i class=\"fa fa-rocket\" style=\"color: #0b93c4; font-size: 30px;\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>  <strong>2017</strong></h3>\r\nUoM Leos were awarded for being the most outstanding University Leo club of the Leo Multiple district 306 – Sri Lanka, Under the Leadership of Leo Shehan Akmeemana, from PMDP Leo Rajitha Abeygunasekara.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1455\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1455 uomimage\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/14th-Ins-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> 14th Installation Ceremony - 2017[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1457\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"uomimage wp-image-1457\" src=\"http://www.uomleos.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/bestleoclub_winning-300x207.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"276\" /> Most Outstanding University Leo Club winners on the stage[/caption]', 'Journey Towards Excellence', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1368-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-01-02 18:09:39', '2018-01-02 12:39:39', '', 1368, 'http://www.uomleos.org/2018/01/02/1368-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1545, 2, '2018-01-02 18:15:04', '2018-01-02 12:45:04', '<div class=\"section-title\">\r\n<h2 id=\"about-header\" style=\"text-align: center;\">SOME WORDS ABOUT  \"<strong>UOM LEOS\" </strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p class=\"intro\" style=\"margin-left: 10px; text-align: center;\">Leo Club of University of Moratuwa is one of the best clubs in Leo District 306 A2 Sri Lanka from its inception. A set of undergraduates from University of Moratuwa, who were fed up with their regular academic work looking for a change formed the club in early 2003.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"about-list\" style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\r\n 	<li><strong>Mission</strong></li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Create enthusiastic Young Leaders, Through Community Service</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li> <strong>Awards</strong></li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Most Outstanding University Leo Club of Sri Lanka  -  Leostic year (2016/2017)</li>\r\n 	<li>Most Outstanding Leo Club of Sri Lanka  -  Leostic year (2015/2016 2013/2014,2011/2012)</li>\r\n 	<li>Most Outstanding Leo Club of District 306 A2  -  Leostic year (2015/2016,2013/2014,2012/2013, 2011/2012, 2008/2009, 2007/2008, 2006/2007, 2005/2006)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '30-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-01-02 18:15:04', '2018-01-02 12:45:04', '', 30, 'http://www.uomleos.org/2018/01/02/30-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
